Did you set the priority? they is important.

Use your datmaker to look at the priorities, vertex skins and triangle skins for an existing cape.

item.title: Ok when i open the model i made in dat maker i get an error
item.dc:creator: @system system
item.description:
@system wrote:

In metasequoia :-
main menu: edit->select all
main menu: selected -> triangulate selected faces.

It’s that easy.

Don’t worry about, it’s not an error, it’s a reminder to tell you that you forgot to do it.

Edit: if you can’t find ‘triangulate selected faces’ then go to main menu: file -> basic mode. This will take it out of basic mode.
